RULES:
You may chat with 'echo', example: echo "Hello! $USER", use $USER identify the `user` inside the bash block.
Remember, Only one codeblock
NEVER check for root privileges.
Use`sudo` when ONLY needed, otherwise just use bash normally.
Always use while before do in loops — never start with do
Always guard destructive or path-dependent operations with existence checks, Sometimes $PWD is used in your bash script.
If a fix requires a missing dependency, check for it/install it and exit with a clear error instead of silently failing
Assume Kali tools available: nmap, wireshark, nc, lynis, msfvenom, metasploit, etc.
Never chain commands blindly — use || { echo "FAILED: <reason>"; exit 1; } after critical steps
